Java mein Data Types (Hinglish mein vyakhya)

1. Primitive Data Types:

   byte:
   - 8-bit poornaank
   - Range: -128 se 127
   - Chote poornaakon ke liye upyogi

   short:
   - 16-bit poornaank
   - Range: -32,768 se 32,767
   - Byte se bade, lekin int se chote poornaakon ke liye

   int:
   - 32-bit poornaank
   - Range: -2^31 se 2^31-1
   - Samanya poornaakon ke liye sabse adhik upyog kiya jaane wala

   long:
   - 64-bit poornaank
   - Range: -2^63 se 2^63-1
   - Bahut bade poornaakon ke liye

   float:
   - 32-bit dashamlav sankhya
   - Ek-parishuddhata waale dashamlav ankon ke liye
   - 'f' ya 'F' pratyay ka upyog karein (jaise 3.14f)

   double:
   - 64-bit dashamlav sankhya
   - Do-parishuddhata waale dashamlav ankon ke liye
   - Default dashamlav prakar

   boolean:
   - Kewal do maan: true ya false
   - Sharton aur logic ke liye upyog kiya jaata hai

   char:
   - Ek 16-bit Unicode varn
   - Range: '\u0000' (0) se '\uffff' (65,535)

2. Reference Data Types:

   String:
   - Varnon ki shrinkhalaa
   - Technically ek class, lekin vishesh vyavahaar ke saath

   Arrays:
   - Samaan prakar ke tattvon ka nishchit-aakaar ka sangrah
   - Ek ya adhik dimensions mein ho sakte hain

   Classes:
   - Upyogkarta-paribhashit data prakar
   - Objects ke liye templates

   Interfaces:
   - Vidhiyon ka amurt sangrah
   - Classes dwara laagu kiye jaate hain

Mahatvapurn Bindhu:
- Primitive types seedhe memory mein sangrihit hote hain aur adhik kushal hote hain.
- Reference types memory mein objects ke pate sangrihit karte hain.
- String class Java mein vishesh hai aur aksar primitive type ki tarah vyavahaar karti hai.
- Java mein Arrays objects hain, bale hi ve primitive types ko dhaaran karte hon.

Upyog ke Udaharan:
int age = 25;
double height = 5.9;
boolean isStudent = true;
String name = "Rahul";
int[] marks = {85, 90, 78, 92, 88};